# Design System Rules — photography-to-ui

This rule defines the **usage constraints** for the visual system. It does NOT
define token values — those live in the W3C DTCG source and would drift if
duplicated here.

> **Source of truth for token VALUES:** `tokens/` (DTCG JSON) → generated
> `tokens/dist/tokens.css` (dark on `:root`) + `tokens/dist/tokens.light.css`
> (`[data-theme='light']`). Browse them in the docs catalog
> (`/photography-to-ui/docs/`, Tokens tab: name, ref, resolved hex per mode, AA).
> The authoritative agent docs are `tokens/CLAUDE.md` and each consumer's
> `CLAUDE.md`. Note: Cursor loads *these* `.cursor/rules`; Claude Code loads the
> `CLAUDE.md` files instead — keep both pointing at `tokens/` so they agree.

Do **not invent** scales, token namespaces, or one-off visual constants. Consume
tokens via `var(--…)`; never hardcode hex/rgba/px for color, spacing, or type
(the coverage checker rejects it). If a token is missing, add it in `tokens/`.

---

## 1) Color System

### 1.1 Brand palette (five ramps × 5 stops)

Magenta (accent), Sky, Frost, Sand, Ink — all derived from photography. Dark is
the default; light is a sparse override. Concrete stop values are in
`tokens/color/primitives.json`; consume the semantic roles below, not raw stops.

### 1.2 Semantic roles (use these in components)

Reference by name; values resolve per mode from the DTCG source:

- `--color-bg-canvas`, `--color-bg-surface` — backgrounds
- `--color-text-primary` / `-secondary` / `-muted` — text hierarchy (all AA+)
- `--color-text-accent` — accent-colored text; `--color-text-cool` — cool/links/code
- `--color-text-on-accent` — text on accent fills
- `--color-accent` — the accent fill/ring (never a large text color)
- `--color-border-subtle` / `-strong` (decorative), `--color-border-accent*` (interactive, ≥3:1)

Contrast obligations are enforced by `check-contrast.mjs` (text ≥4.5:1, non-text
UI ≥3:1) in both modes — see the docs Audit tab.

### 1.3 Color Usage Rules (Strict)
- **Magenta is never a large background fill.**
- Accent is reserved for intent:
  - focus rings
  - inline affordances (links, small buttons)
  - tiny indicators (dots, markers, thin rules)
- Frost is the **thinking space** (canvas).
- Sand is for **surfaces** (panels/containers).
- Prefer borders/dividers over shadows.
- Do not use gradients, neon glows, or "highlight washes" as decoration.

### 1.4 Color Family Semantics

**MAGENTA — Brand Core**
- Identity color: bold, feminine, tech-forward, high-impact
- Palette Name: Cucusa Magenta
- Purpose: Accents, highlights, data viz, brand UI
- Usage: Focus rings, interactive elements, emphasis (never large background fills)

**FROST — Pure Surfaces**
- Snow, ice, clean light aesthetic
- Palette Name: Cucusa Frost
- Purpose: Pure surfaces for photography-based brand aesthetic
- Dark Mode: Darker shades (Frost-1, Frost-2) for surfaces and backgrounds
- Light Mode: Frost-5 canvas, clean light surfaces

**SAND — Warm Neutrals**
- From Madrid photos
- Brings humanity, softness, grounding
- Palette Name: Cucusa Sand
- Purpose: Warm surfaces, grounding elements
- Dark Mode: Darker shades (Sand-1, Sand-2) for subtle warmth in backgrounds
- Light Mode: Sand-5 surfaces — warm panel backgrounds

**SKY — Cool, Calm Blues**
- Extracted from snow/forest photos
- Palette Name: Cucusa Sky
- Purpose: Backgrounds, calm surfaces, balancing magenta
- Dark Mode: Darkest shades (Sky-1, Sky-2) for canvas and primary backgrounds
- Light Mode: Sky-2 for cool text, Sky-4/5 in light gradients

**INK — Neutrals & Text System**
- Clarity, structure, engineering layer
- Palette Name: Cucusa Ink
- Purpose: Text, foregrounds, shadows, contrast surfaces
- Dark Mode: Lighter shades (Ink-4, Ink-5) for text on dark backgrounds
- Light Mode: Ink-1 primary, Ink-2 secondary text

### 1.5 Mode-Specific Semantics

**Dark Mode:**
- Canvas: Sky-1 (darkest blue)
- Surfaces: Frost-1 (dark neutral) or Sky-1 with opacity
- Text: Ink-5 (lightest) for primary, Ink-4 for secondary, Ink-3 for muted
- Borders: White with opacity (12% subtle, 24% strong)

**Light Mode (shipped — sparse overrides in tokens/modes/light/):**
- Canvas: Frost-5 #f7f7fb (Frost is the thinking space)
- Surfaces: Sand-5 #f5efea (Sand warms the panels)
- Text: Ink-1 primary (16.3:1), Ink-2 secondary (8.3:1), Frost-2 muted (4.9:1 — Ink-3 fails on light)
- Accent text: Magenta-1 (the deep stop, 6.4:1) — mirrors dark mode's Magenta-4
- Cool text: Sky-2 (7.7:1) — mirrors dark mode's Sky-4
- Borders: accent ladder rebuilt on Magenta-2 at 65/70/75/80% into canvas, all ≥3:1
- Glows at half strength; shadows soften (the glow idiom is dark-only)
- Mode mechanism: `[data-theme='light']` on `<html>`; dark is the default `:root`
- Enforced by `npm run check:contrast` — 44 checks across both modes in CI

