## 2) Typography System

### 2.1 Font Family (Single Font Only)
```css
:root{
  --font-family-base: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
}
```

### 2.2 Weights (Limited)
```css
:root{
  --font-weight-regular: 400;
  --font-weight-medium: 500;
  --font-weight-bold: 600;
}
```

### 2.3 Type Scale — Perfect Fifth (1.5), Base 16px
```css
:root{
  --text-xs: 0.667rem;  /* ~10.7px */
  --text-sm: 0.889rem;  /* ~14.2px */
  --text-md: 1rem;      /* 16px */
  --text-lg: 1.5rem;    /* 24px */
  --text-xl: 2.25rem;   /* 36px */
  --text-xxl: 3.375rem; /* 54px — use sparingly; avoid hero theatrics */
}
```

### 2.3.1 Display / Experimental Scale — Golden Ratio-inspired
**Separate from core token scale. For experimental hero moments only.**

```css
:root{
  --display-xl: 5.46rem;  /* ~87.4px — Golden Ratio from xxl (3.375 × 1.618) */
}
```

**Usage Rules:**
- **Experimental only** — not part of core design system
- Reserved for hero moments (e.g., full-bleed intro phrases overlaying photos)
- `--display-xl`: Fixed size, Golden Ratio progression from `--text-xxl`
- **Monospace constraint**: Display XL is the practical maximum for monospace fonts. Larger sizes become too heavy and lose the technical aesthetic.
- Use sparingly and intentionally — this is a display size, not body text

### 2.4 Line-height + Letter-spacing (Minimal, Intentional)
```css
:root{
  --line-height-tight: 1.2;
  --line-height-base: 1.45;
  --line-height-loose: 1.7;

  --letter-spacing-tight: -0.02em;
  --letter-spacing-normal: 0em;
}
```

### 2.5 Typography Usage Rules
- One font family only; hierarchy via size, weight, spacing, contrast.
- Avoid oversized hero typography; `--text-xxl` should be rare.
- No decorative text treatments (shadows, outlines, gradients).
- Avoid ALL CAPS except short labels (≤ 12 chars).
- Prefer short, declarative headings; avoid long “marketing” headlines.

---

## 3) Spacing System (Intent-based, Fixed Set)

```css
:root{
  --space-xs: 0.25rem; /* micro separation */
  --space-sm: 0.5rem;  /* related items */
  --space-md: 1rem;    /* grouping */
  --space-lg: 2rem;    /* breathing room */
  --space-xl: 4rem;    /* structural separation */
}
```

Spacing rules:
- Do not introduce additional spacing scales.
- Use spacing to communicate hierarchy (content feels **placed**, not stacked).
- Prefer fewer, larger separations over many small gaps.

---

## 4) Shape, Dividers, Elevation

### 4.1 Radius (Soft, restrained)
```css
:root{
  --radius-sm: 10px;
  --radius-md: 14px;
}
```

### 4.2 Dividers (Preferred over shadows)
```css
:root{
  --divider-subtle: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  --divider-strong: 1px solid var(--color-border-strong);
}
```

### 4.3 Elevation (Minimal)
```css
:root{
  --shadow-1: 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
  --shadow-2: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
}
```

Elevation rules:
- Prefer dividers/borders; shadows must stay subtle.
- Do not create “stacked card” aesthetics.
- Do not use heavy drop-shadows or blurred glows.

---

## 5) Focus Ring (A11y + Brand Signal)

```css
:root{
  --focus-ring-width: 2px;
  --focus-ring-offset: 2px;
  --focus-ring-color: var(--color-magenta);
}
```

Rules:
- Focus ring must be visible on all interactive elements.
- Use the magenta focus ring consistently as the “intent” signal.
- Never remove focus outlines without providing an equivalent visible ring.

---

## 6) Assets & Pattern Usage (Photography + Ovals + LEGO/Grid)

### 6.1 Photography Rules
Photography is **context**, not content.

Use photography as:
- cropped planes
- subdued background fields
- side-context blocks inside the Primary Panel

Never:
- full-bleed hero images
- wallpaper / repeated backgrounds
- attention-stealing overlays

Practical defaults:
- Reduce prominence via opacity/contrast reduction; blur only if necessary and subtle.
- Ensure text remains readable without relying on photo content.

### 6.2 Oval Pattern Rules
Meaning: softness, rhythm, human interruption.

Use sparingly:
- **max 1 oval moment per panel**
- clipped edges or small inserts

Never:
- tile or repeat as wallpaper
- place behind primary text
- animate beyond opacity

### 6.3 LEGO/Grid Pattern Rules
Meaning: modularity, construction, systems thinking.

Use only in:
- insight containers
- dividers
- headers/labels within the Insight Rail

Never:
- as global background wallpaper
- behind primary text
- as the main visual focal point

### 6.4 Pattern Global Rules
- Patterns annotate thinking; they do not decorate surfaces.
- Patterns must not animate beyond opacity.
- Patterns must not compete with photography.

---

## 7) Token Discipline (Non-negotiable)

- Use ONLY tokens defined in this rule for:
  - colors and semantic roles
  - typography (font, scale, metrics)
  - spacing
  - radius
  - dividers
  - shadows
  - focus rings
- Do not introduce new token namespaces or “one-off” constants in components.
- If a new token is needed, add it here (this file) deliberately with a rationale.
- Avoid duplicate tokens that mean the same thing.

